{
  "stem": "7506.4",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And when they passed one of the kitchens in the camp, in the whole camp, the kitchen-- not in the Sternlager, there were no the kitchens, but in the other part of the camp-- he had picked up some spring onions from the floor that were the garbage, but he picked it up.",
      "word_count": 53
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And an SS saw him do it and beat him, and they put him in the bunker for-- what do you call it in English?",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "In Dutch, it's [SPEAKING DUTCH].",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It's like into jail.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I know now that people were beaten up very badly in the bunker.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And one day, I was playing on the appellplatz with some other boys.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I don't know whether my father heard me or whether I called his name, but I remember talking to my father through-- I was outside.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He was inside.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But there must have been opening enough, either an air vent or something where he could hear me playing outside with the children, and we spoke very shortly to each other.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I think from that time on and around about that time, for me things started to change.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Also what happened, my Uncle Sam, my cousin's father, died.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "He died in the camp.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "That's my Auntie Annie's husband, my mother's brother-in-law.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I remember that we-- I remember myself with other men walking along the barbed wire of the camp, which was on the side of the main road through the camp, to the crematorium.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Because there was a crematorium in Belsen.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And occasionally, you could smell the smell of burning corpses.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "We walked, a group of men, while on the other side of the barbed wire was a horse drawn like a farmer's wagon with what I understood then to be my uncle's body.",
      "word_count": 33
    }
  ],
